3 Hours Ago The Kaduna State Police Command’s Public Relations Officer, Mohammed Jalige, ASP, confirmed the attack, noting that it took place last night. This is coming barely less than 48 hours after the State Commissioner for Internal Security and Home Affairs, Mr. Samuel Aruwan, presented the 2020 security situation reports to the state governor, Malam Nasir El-Rufai. In that report, the commissioner had said bandits killed no fewer than 937 persons, kidnapped 1,972 persons, and rustled 7,195 cattle in the state in 2020.



